    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_42180_1841_03_01_page01.jpg"/>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#North-Audley-Street-1_ENK">1 North Audley Street</placeName>
                        <date when="1841-03-01">March 1<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>1841</date></dateline>
                    <salute>
                        Dear Sir
                    </salute>
                </opener>
                <p>
                   
                    I have before me a note of<lb/>
                    your daughters apologising<lb/>
                    for your not coming to see<lb/>
                    me - you and your son<lb/>
                    both owe me the courtesy<lb/>
                    of a visit - which I must<lb/>
                    have now or never as I<lb/>
                    have but this week more<lb/>
                    of <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#London_ENK">London</placeName> life - But it is<lb/>
                    not the mere ceremony of <choice> 
                    <orig>visit<lb/>
                    ing</orig>
                    <reg>visiting</reg>
                    </choice>
                    upon which I stand; I<lb/>
                    w<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> not take you from solid<lb/>
                    business to empty morning<lb/>
                    visit - But I want to see<lb/>
                    you both or either to have<lb/>
                    a half hours <hi rend="underline">talk</hi> with you<lb/>
                    upon a literary project of<lb/>
                    my friend <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BellX2">Madame Bellois</persName><lb/>
                    -It is not about a book<lb/></p>
                
                    <p>
                    But tho I tell what it is not<lb/>
                    about I cannot tell you what<lb/>
                    it is about till <del>you</del> we can talk<lb/>
                    it over - It is too long for<lb/>
                    
                    <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_42180_1841_03_01_page02.jpg"/>
                    
                    
                    writing notes upon<lb/></p>
                    <p>
                    I trust that either you or<lb/>
                    your son understand<lb/>
                    French &amp; whichever <choice> 
                    <orig>under<lb/>
                    stands</orig>
                     <reg>understands</reg>
                     </choice>
                    it best had best<lb/>
                    read <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BellX2">Madame Bellois</persName><lb/>
                    letter - or <unclear></unclear> to the<lb/>
                    translation of<lb/></p>
                   <closer>D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Sir- yours truly<lb/>
                    <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName><lb/></closer>
                    <postscript>
                    <p> <hi rend="underline">P.S</hi> Do not come to day!<lb/>
                     <del><unclear>even if you could</unclear></del> because<lb/>
                     I am engaged all morning<lb/>
                     till four<lb/>
                            
                     <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_42180_1841_03_01_page03.jpg"/>
                            
                     / Monday, unless you could come<lb/>
                       <hi rend="underline">between 4 and 5</hi><lb/> </p>
                    </postscript>
               
            </div>
        </body>
        <back> </back>
